2. COMPILATION ERRORS (WILL FAIL TO BUILD)
===========================================

ERROR A: Server.hs line 94-95 — Type mismatch: Maybe (Maybe ByteString)
         vs Maybe Text in ListObjects routing
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
  File: /home/.../src/S3OSS/Server.hs, lines 94-95

  Code:
    let prefix = lookup "prefix" q
        delimiter = lookup "delimiter" q

  Problem:
    `queryString req` returns `Query = [(ByteString, Maybe ByteString)]`.
    `lookup` on this type yields `Maybe (Maybe ByteString)`.
    But `handleListObjects` (List/Handler.hs line 17) expects
    `Maybe Text` for both `prefix` and `delimiter`.

  The types `Maybe (Maybe ByteString)` and `Maybe Text` are incompatible
  with no implicit conversion. This WILL cause a GHC type error.

  Fix needed: Each lookup result must be decoded from ByteString to Text,
  e.g.:
    prefix = lookup "prefix" q >>= fmap (decodeUtf8With lenientDecode)

  Similarly for `delimiter` on line 95.


ERROR B: Server.hs line 96 — Type mismatch in maxKeys computation
-----------------------------------------------------------------
  File: /home/.../src/S3OSS/Server.hs, line 96

  Code:
    maxKeys = lookup "max-keys" q >>= readMaybe . T.unpack

  Problem:
    `lookup "max-keys" q :: Maybe (Maybe ByteString)`.
    The `>>=` unwraps the outer Maybe, so the RHS receives
    `Maybe ByteString`, not `Text`. But `readMaybe . T.unpack :: Text -> Maybe Int`.
    Applying this to `Maybe ByteString` is a type error.

  Fix needed: The inner `Maybe ByteString` must also be unwrapped, e.g.:
    maxKeys = lookup "max-keys" q >>= (>>= readMaybe . T.unpack . decodeUtf8With lenientDecode)

  Or more clearly:
    maxKeys = do
      mbs <- lookup "max-keys" q
      bs  <- mbs
      readMaybe (T.unpack (TE.decodeUtf8With lenientDecode bs))


ERROR C (LIKELY): Server.hs line 113 — putObject dataDir (requestBody req)
                — ConduitT base monad mismatch
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
  File: /home/.../src/S3OSS/Server.hs, line 113

  Code:
    (sha256, size, etag) <- putObject dataDir (requestBody req)

  Problem (needs verification against installed wai version):
    `putObject :: FilePath -> ConduitT () ByteString IO () -> IO (...)`
    `requestBody :: Request -> Source IO ByteString`
    where `Source m o = ConduitT () o m ()`

    If wai's `Source` is exactly `ConduitT () ByteString IO ()`, then
    the types match. But some wai versions use `ResourceT IO` as the
    base monad. If the monads differ, this is a type error.

  Verdict: Likely OK for wai >= 3.2 where Source uses pure IO, but
  should be confirmed during build.


