3. CRITICAL LOGIC BUGS (COMPILE OK, WRONG BEHAVIOR)
====================================================

BUG 1: Auth bypass in ALL handler modules — `unless` doesn't guard
------------------------------------------------------------------
  Affected files:
    /home/.../src/S3OSS/Bucket/Handler.hs  (lines 19-20, 31-32, 41-42, 52-53)
    /home/.../src/S3OSS/Object/Handler.hs  (lines 24-25, 36-37, 54-55, 68-69, 83-84)
    /home/.../src/S3OSS/List/Handler.hs    (lines 19-20)
    /home/.../src/S3OSS/Multipart/Handler.hs (lines 23-24, 37-38, 50-51, 71-72)

  Pattern in all handlers (e.g. handleCreateBucket):
    unless (evaluate (userPolicies user) S3CreateBucket (bucketARN name)) $
      pure $ errorResponse status403 "AccessDenied" "Access Denied"
    result <- createBucket store name    -- CONTINUES EXECUTING!

  Root cause:
    `unless cond action` evaluates to `if cond then pure () else action`.
    The `pure $ errorResponse ...` produces `IO Response` and returns `()`.
    The `()` is discarded by the `do` block, and execution continues to
    the NEXT LINE unconditionally. The error response is computed but
    NEVER RETURNED TO THE CALLER.

  Impact:
    EVERY authorization check in the entire service is a no-op. Any
    request succeeds regardless of user policies. This is a severe
    security vulnerability.

  Fix:
    Replace the `unless` pattern with a guard that short-circuits:
      let allowed = evaluate (userPolicies user) S3CreateBucket (bucketARN name)
      if not allowed
        then pure $ errorResponse status403 "AccessDenied" "Access Denied"
        else do
          result <- createBucket store name
          ...

    Or using a helper function:
      guardAuthorized :: Bool -> Response -> IO Response -> IO Response
      guardAuthorized True  _        action = action
      guardAuthorized False errResp _       = pure errResp


