6. CIRCULAR IMPORT ANALYSIS
============================

Module import graph (simplified):
  S3OSS.Prelude -> base, rio, text, bytestring (no project deps)
  S3OSS.Types -> Prelude (via RIO), aeson, GHC.Generics
  S3OSS.XML -> Prelude, Types, text, xml-conduit
  S3OSS.Config -> Prelude, Types, yaml
  S3OSS.Store -> Prelude, Types, sqlite-simple
  S3OSS.Object.Storage -> Prelude, Types, crypton, conduit
  S3OSS.Auth.Policy -> Prelude, Types
  S3OSS.Auth.SigV4 -> Prelude, Types, crypton, wai
  S3OSS.Bucket.Handler -> Prelude, Types, Store, XML, Auth.Policy, wai
  S3OSS.Object.Handler -> Prelude, Types, Store, Object.Storage, XML, Auth.Policy, wai
  S3OSS.List.Handler -> Prelude, Types, Store, XML, Auth.Policy, wai
  S3OSS.Multipart.Manager -> Prelude, Types, Store, Object.Storage, XML, crypton, conduit, random
  S3OSS.Multipart.Handler -> Prelude, Types, Store, Multipart.Manager, XML, Auth.Policy, wai
  S3OSS.Presigned -> Prelude, Types, crypton
  S3OSS.Server -> Prelude, Types, Config, Store, Auth.SigV4, all Handlers,
                  wai, warp, conduit, bytestream

  VERDICT: NO circular imports detected. The dependency graph is a
  directed acyclic graph (DAG). Server.hs sits at the top, importing
  from all leaf modules. The only concern is that three modules
  (Bucket/Handler, Object/Handler, Multipart/Handler) all define
  their own `errorResponse`, but these are independent definitions
  in different modules so no circular dependency arises.


